.TH "_kvm_vz_save_htimer" 9 "_kvm_vz_save_htimer" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
_kvm_vz_save_htimer \- Switch to software emulation of guest timer.
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "void" _kvm_vz_save_htimer
.BI "(struct kvm_vcpu *vcpu "  ","
.BI "u32 *out_compare "  ","
.BI "u32 *out_cause "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "vcpu" 12
Virtual CPU.
.IP "out_compare" 12
-- undescribed --
.IP "out_cause" 12
-- undescribed --
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Save VZ guest timer state and switch to software emulation of guest CP0
timer. The hard timer must already be in use, so preemption should be
disabled.
